args: Look, Commander. The owner of this\nvillage gave us some fresh fruit.
I see. Place it there, then.
What a preposterous idea. Why should\nI give any thought to a traitor?
I know you've always looked up to him.
When, exactly, did I say that?
You didn't, but it's not hard to tell.

The two of you are polar opposites.
If he believes something is right, he'll
see it done—even it means punching
a government official and getting demoted.
*sigh* He needs to learn to act\nlike he's in the military. A soldier...
...Must always execute orders without\nquestion. I've heard that from you a\nthousand times.
But I don't think you believe it as strongly\nas you used to.
You should be more honest with yourself.
A soldier acting for themselves can only\nlead to tragedy.
The incident ten years ago is proof\nenough of that.
Ten Years Earlier\nA Town in Svenitlan Territory
We've been ordered to retreat?!\nBut that makes no sense!
HQ has decided to give up on suppressing\nthe insurgents for now.
But there are still civilians in the town!\nWhat will become of them?!

Until HQ officially declares their intent to
abandon this land, they will have value
as hostages. Our foes will keep them
alive for the time being.
How can you talk about them like...like\npieces on a BOARD?! Are you really\nokay with this?!
NO! I'm not! But we are not equipped to\nfight a war of attrition.

We should retreat before we come under
attack, and reorganize from a distance
before striking again. That is the most
logical course.
It might be logical, but do you think\nit's RIGHT?
Mister Soldier, you have to help us!
What is it? Are you all right?
S-some scary people took my mommy\nand daddy... You gotta help them!\nPlease!
Please! Don't let those people hurt them!
...Sorry, Kirsty. I'm gonna have to\ndisregard those orders.
So am I. I'd never forgive myself\nif I turned my back on a crying kid.
Please, don't do this!\nYou'll be branded criminals!
If that's the cost of doing what's right,\nthen so be it.
＂One can only find justice within their\nown heart.＂ That's what Victor always\nsays, and he's right!
I agree with you, I do. But now is not\nthe time for this!
Go ahead and lead the other soldiers\nout of here to regroup.
Then, when we wander along after,\nyou can give us a proper scolding.
See you on the other side, Kirsty!

In the end, both soldiers were captured during
the rescue effort. The girl was then used as
a hostage to extract information from them
about their unit.
In the resulting attack, Kirsty's unit was forced\nto abandon the town. Its residents were\nslaughtered without exception.
Your comrades were fools. Their inability\nto follow orders cost this nation greatly,\nnever mind their own lives.
Entertaining individual whims can only\nlead to ruin. Remember that well.
From that point on, Kirsty resolved\nto obey her orders without question.
For if her comrades had only done the same,\nthe tragedy that ensued could have been avoided...
...I must have dozed off. It's been\nsome time since I had that dream.
